'''Corulag Academy''', formally the '''Corulag Imperial Military Academy''', was an educational military institution in [[Curamelle/Legends|Curamelle]], the capital city of [[Corulag/Legends|Corulag]]. It was created before the rise of the Empire, however, and served the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic's]] [[Republic Army|Army]] before the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. It had a Science Service tower then, which was infiltrated by [[Bartokk]] [[Assassin/Legends|assassins]] to capture [[Teela Panjarra]] for [[Frexton]]. After [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] took power, the Academy was a branch of the Empire-wide [[Imperial Academy/Legends|military school]]. Among the known students at the academy was the man known as [[Starter]], who was eventually expelled due to obnoxious and undisciplined behavior, and [[Juno Eclipse/Legends|Juno Eclipse]], a woman who went on to lead [[Black Eight Squadron]] then became the personal pilot of [[Galen Marek]].

The Academy trained members of both the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]] and the [[Imperial Army/Legends|Army]] in undergraduate and graduate degrees. In addition, the specific fields within the Academy were navy midshipmen, army cadets, flight school pilots, and specialists from all services within the Imperial Military. It also accepted Graduates from both Raithal and Prefsbelt Academies. A branch of the Navy's training program was also located on Corulag's largest [[Moon/Legends|moon]].

